members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.blockedURI
members.description: The URI of the resource blocked because it violates a policy.

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.disposition
members.description: Indicates how the violated policy is configured to be treated by the user agent. This will be "enforce" or "report".

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.documentURI
members.description: The URI of the document or worker in which the violation was found.

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.effectiveDirective
members.description: The string representing the directive whose enforcement uncovered the violation.

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.LineNumber
members.description: The line number in the document or worker at which the violation occurred.

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.originalPolicy
members.description: A string containing the policy whose enforcement uncovered the violation.

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.referrer
members.description: The referrer of the resources whose policy was violated. This will be a URL or null.

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.sourceFile
members.description: The URI of the document or worker in which the violation was found.

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.statusCode
members.description: The HTTP status code of the document or worker in which the violation occurred.

members.name: SecurityPolicyViolationEvent.violatedDirective
members.description: The string representing the directive whose enforcement uncovered the violation.
